FOODBORNE ILLNESS - USA: (CALIFORNIA), NEUROLOGICAL SYMPTOMS, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 7 Jan 2015
Source: KABC [edited]
http://abc7.com/news/orange-county-bakerys-permit-suspended-due-to-cockroach-infestation/466264/


An Orange County, CA bakery was closed after 30 people fell ill after eating Rosca de Reyes, a fruit cake traditionally eaten on 6 Jan 2015, known as Three Kings Day or Epiphany. The cake was distributed countywide by Cholula's Bakery in Santa Ana to nearly a dozen different locations.

Those affected complained of dizziness, palpitations and numbness. "I had never felt so terrified, like I didn't even know what was going on with me," said one person from Santa Ana who was affected. Paramedics rushed her to the hospital because she felt dizzy, numb and her heart was racing. "I was hallucinating... I almost felt like I was not in my body," she said.

Helene Calvet, deputy health counselor for the Orange County Health Agency, says the symptoms are not contagious. "Some people had symptoms as soon as 20 minutes after eating the bread; we don't think it's like a infectious agent so we're looking at other agents," Calvet said.

The Orange County Health Department and Santa Ana police officers spent Wednesday morning, 7 Jan 2015, at the bakery. Health officials closed the store and suspended its permit, citing traces of cockroach infestation. The owner of Cholula's Bakery refused to speak to Eyewitness News.

The cake was sold at the following markets in southern California on Monday and Tuesday [5-6 Jan 2015]:
Cholula's Bakery Santa Ana; El Nopal Mercado San Juan Capistrano; La Bodega Ranch Orange, CA; La Bodega Ranch Fullerton; Santa Ana Marquet Santa Ana; Tony's Liquor San Juan Capistrano; Gonzalez Marquet Placentia; Taqueria Mocorito Restaurant Anaheim; Taco Boy Anaheim; Brianna's Ice Cream Anaheim; La Bodega Ranch Market Long Beach.

The Orange County Health Department is not treating this as a criminal investigation, but retailers and consumers were told to throw out any Rosca de Reyes from Cholula's Bakery.

[Byline: Greg Lee]

